column5: Heres one that i caught on a rap  popper in 3 feet of water  under neath a tree branch just touching the water.
Why tell WHERE U caught it?? U don't have enough pressure there? Anyway,  U -D - Man!
nice fish , what was the weight ?
i caught it by the bolsover swing bridge if you now the area i was around the island right when you enter the canal. it was 5 1/4lb  21"
ill try to get a map of lake.
I fish that lake quite a bit. My boat is at my grandparents on the top part of the lake. Fishing has been getting slower each year since they moved there ( 9 years?)
its a great lake to fish with young kids doesn't get rough not very deep (sorry danbo new to sight not used to this posting stuff)
I'm sorry too! It's one of my fave lakes too!  Cheers & Welcome aboard..
Nice catch man, topwater is the way to go!  Congrads, MTBF
Nice fish. I never knew about that spot. Just may head down there tonight
